<br>
Void is a 10 pt style with a 10 minute timer.  Doesn't matter how high the To-Hit and Damage is, or that it has Medium Defense...there's no place on our hotbars and it's not worth buying.<br>
<br>
We have plenty of styles already, don't need more.<br>
<br>
Change Void (and other light tank class specific RA's) and make it into a Weaponskill boost (100 pts, or whatever is deemed balanced) that also halves your style endurance use for it's duration (whatever is deemed balanced).  Something like that would start to make a 10 point RA worth buying.<br>
<br>
Increased Weaponskill is effectively an increase in To-Hit bonus, as well as an increase in Defense (more evade/parry).  Endurance cost decreased would make end hog styles like Misty Gloom useable (for those that aren't slash spec) for the duration of the RA. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=uhno>uhno</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.grumbled.com/images/paradoxicon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#000000>(6/27/03 4:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=268.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unique RA</span><hr size=1> We don't need a unique RA as much as we need access to ones that already exist.<br>
